            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello! I'm using code bellow\r\n{code}\r\n<?php\r\n\r\nset_include_path(get_include_path() . PATH_SEPARATOR . '.\/lib');\r\ninclude_once 'Zend\/Markup.php';\r\n\r\n$bbcode = Zend_Markup::factory('Bbcode');\r\n\r\n$input = <<<EOT\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.markup.getting-started.html\r\nEOT;\r\n\r\n$text = $bbcode->render($input);\r\nvar_dump($text);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nReturn\r\n{code}\r\nstring(68) \"http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.markup.getting-started.html\"\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIt would be nice that links detects automaticly (we can enable\/disable this feature in options).\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nstring(xx) \"<a href=\"http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.markup.getting-started.html\">http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/...started.html<\/a>\"\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso I propose add method *attachLinks*, wich will return string with wrapped links with tag _url_:\r\n{code}\r\nstring(xx) \"[url=\"http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.markup.getting-started.html\"]http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/...started.html[\/url]\"\r\n{code}"
